records.addlTxt:
Defendant Brandon Lee St. George in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  @ 1:50 pm.  State gives plea agreement, Information on Filed, withheld sentence 3 years probation, sexual offender evaluation, counseling, costs, 1 year jail. Jail can be served in South Dakota, Can moves to reopen & amended if completes probation & new DA may not accept offer, Atty Laufenberg explains that reopen will not be automatic, Defense free to argue jail. Def. agrees to plea agreement. Plea questionnaire & waiver of rights filed. Def. understand charge & penalties.  Cause Child of View Sex Activity, no contest plea. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Def. understand elements.  Atty Laufenberg is satisfied. Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given. Factual basis stipulated. Court finds factual basis, accepts plea & finds def. Guilty to Cause Child to view sex activity, 948.055(1). Complied with Victim rights. J.B. gives statement.  State gives sentencing argument.  Atty Laufenberg gives sentencing argument. Def. makes statement. Court questions both sides.  Court did receive letter from wife, current employer, JJ Constructions & from pastor & has reviewed.  Court gives statement, Atty Laufenberg would like to take recess to get photo, State gives statement.  Court will not take a recess. Court continues and orders
withheld prison sentence 3 years probation, Completing Sexual Offender Evaluation, Completing any Counseling required by agent, Costs, DNA Sample & 250 surcharge, Court will authorize or approve probation be served in South Dakota, Reopen to amend to misdemeanor, Court with authorize, present DA does not object, Def. may petition to reopen & amend to a misdemeanor. Put that wording on JOC. DA does not object. 1 day credit if revoked. 4 months  jail . May be served in the State of South Dakota, no electronic monitoring, Huber privileges. C no later than 3-6-16 @ 6 pm. Def. advised of firearm rights or voting rights.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Def. advised of postconviction rights. Def will need to resume paying atty payment if still owes after bill received, but will not need to make any more payment. Letter  to be put in court file.
